Dashboard Components

Your dashboard contains 4 major visual sections:

1) Shipment Mode Analysis
Chart Type:

Pie Chart

Purpose:

Shows the distribution of shipment methods.

Insights:
Regular Air is used the most
Express Air and Delivery Truck are used less
Helps logistics teams optimize shipping cost
2) Top 5 Profitable States
Chart Type:

Horizontal Bar Chart

Purpose:

Displays the top-performing states based on total profit.

States shown:
Pennsylvania
Florida
Wisconsin
Iowa
California
Business Use:

Helps identify strong-performing markets.

3) Top 3 Least Profitable Products
Chart Type:

Horizontal Bar Chart

Purpose:

Shows products generating losses or very low profit.

Business Use:
Helps identify poor-performing products
Useful for pricing decisions
Helps reduce inventory waste
4) Top 10 Most Profitable Cities
Chart Type:

Column Chart

Purpose:

Displays cities generating the highest profits.

Business Use:
Identifies top revenue zones
Helps in regional sales strategy
Supports expansion planning
